<p>The importance of expressing sympathy in the workplace cannot be overstated.  The shared work environment fosters a sense of community, and when a colleague experiences loss, the collective support demonstrates empathy and provides a sense of belonging during a difficult time.  A thoughtful condolence message can help alleviate some of the burden and provide a sense of comfort and solidarity.  Consider the colleague's personality and your relationship when crafting your message.  A brief, simple message might suffice for a more distant colleague, while a more personal and detailed message might be appropriate for a close friend.  Always ensure your message is sincere, avoiding any forced or insincere expressions.</p>
    

